# Revision Pass / Structural Revision

When the user says **"Revision Pass on Chapter X"**, **"revise chapter X"**, **"structural revision on chapter X"**, **"apply revision pass to chapter X"**, or similar:

1. Confirm **Revision Pass** stage (or author override) per `Writing_System/Pipeline/solmare_writing_lifecycle.md`.
2. Load the **router only:** `Writing_System/revision_pass.md`
3. Also load as needed: chapter list purpose notes, prior Final Candidate / LOCKED FINAL chapters, `Style_Guide/revision_philosophy.md`, relevant Characters/Universe docs.
4. Run numbered passes **in order**, loading **one pass file at a time** (do not preload all six):
   1. `Writing_System/Revision_Pass/01_people.md`
   2. `Writing_System/Revision_Pass/02_story_structure.md`
   3. `Writing_System/Revision_Pass/03_clarity_language.md`
   4. `Writing_System/Revision_Pass/04_continuity_preflight.md`
   5. `Writing_System/Revision_Pass/05_character.md` (after structure; no plot/scene changes)
   6. `Writing_System/Revision_Pass/06_ai_signature.md` (after Character Pass; strip AI polish)
5. After the last pass run, deliver the **combined report** from the router.

**Standalone triggers:**
- *Character Pass on Chapter X* → Pass 5 only
- *AI Signature Removal Pass on Chapter X* / *AI Signature Pass on Chapter X* → Pass 6 only

## Rules

- **Not Writing Pass 1.** No full Stage 3 polish unless the habit blocks comprehension.
- Prefer surgical fixes. Full people-first rewrite only when Pass 1’s working test fails.
- Working principle: **People create story. Story carries policy.** (People first / story second / policy last retained.)
- Pass 1: people first; character beats; rewrite playbook; competence-before-attraction check (`Revision_Pass/competence_before_attraction.md`).
- Pass 2: story/structure; trust the reader; plant life / payoff later.
- Pass 3: captions, soft-noun ban, jargon, plain speech, name the damn thing.
- Pass 4: successive continuity; protected cast / career (`PROTECTED_RECURRING_CAST.md`); *Veil*/Interface roster; strategic charts; search pass; **mandatory first-hearing preflight**.
- Pass 5: character voice / perspective / behavior; no plot changes.
- Pass 6: AI signature removal — meaning-after-image; over-articulate dialogue; excess narrative certainty; lived body not furniture / no recycled Book One check-ins (§6.4); no new scenes / no drama expansion.
- Author mid-read *what does this mean?* = hard fail — plain-expand immediately.
- Do not duplicate linked canon wholesale — load the canonical file when needed.

Authoritative status table: book `Act_Outlines/chapter_list.md`.
